  "translations": {
    "en": "regarding a man who struck with his sword a camel or a sheep in other than its (proper) slaughter place, and had named (said Bismillah) when he struck. So he said: It is not permissible to eat a slaughtered animal that is not slaughtered from its (proper) slaughter place — meaning when one is deliberate in that and his state is not a state of necessity. But as for when he is compelled to do so and what he intends to slaughter proves difficult for him, then there is no problem with that.",
